---
// One idea: does showing the scaffolding cost you authority — or is being seen
// mid-build the only authority worth trusting?
---
<svg viewBox="0 0 560 180" role="img" aria-labelledby="scaf-t">
  <title id="scaf-t">On the left, a building fully draped in cloth to look finished, its true state hidden. On the right, the same building with its scaffolding openly visible, half-built and honest — and marked as the more trustworthy of the two.</title>
  <!-- draped, hidden -->
  <path class="ink hair" d="M60 130 L 60 60 C 90 48, 120 48, 150 60 L 150 130 Z" opacity="0.6" fill="var(--paper-deep)" />
  <path class="ink hair" d="M72 74 C 96 68, 120 68, 140 74" opacity="0.4" />
  <text class="hand-label" x="58" y="152" font-size="13" opacity="0.7">draped — looks finished</text>
  <!-- scaffolding, honest -->
  <path class="ink block" d="M400 130 L 400 56 L 470 56 L 470 130" />
  <g class="ink hair"><path d="M390 78 L 480 78 M390 104 L 480 104 M414 56 L 414 130 M456 56 L 456 130" stroke="var(--poppy)" opacity="0.7" /></g>
  <path class="ink hair" d="M418 90 L 452 90 L 452 116 L 418 116 Z" opacity="0.6" />
  <circle class="port-fill" cx="435" cy="66" r="3" />
  <text class="hand-label hand-label--accent" x="392" y="152" font-size="13">scaffolding shown — trusted</text>
</svg>
